docs.snippet: When President Eisenhower starts tomorrow on a tour around Latin America that will take him more than 15,000 miles in less than two weeks he will be demonstrating two things: first, that he thinks our southern neighbors are important enough to be...
docs.lead_paragraph: When President Eisenhower starts tomorrow on a tour around Latin America that will take him more than 15,000 miles in less than two weeks he will be demonstrating two things: first, that he thinks our southern neighbors are important enough to be fitted into a final Presidential year that is already sharply scheduled; second that he himself now has the energy to do what he might once have left to the late Secretary Dulles.
